Text: I'm still so grateful for all the child care providers who looked after my boys. But this pandemic has been tough, and many are struggling. We need to pass the #BuildBackBetter plan, invest in our child care workforce, and put affordable child care in reach of every family. https://t.co/MAdDpnv4ar
Please get vaccinated. It could save your life — and help save the lives of our kids, grandparents, and loved ones with compromised immune systems.

We can fight the climate crisis, rebuild communities who have already been hit hard, and build healthier, more resilient communities.

And we'll create millions of good union jobs to get the work done.

We need to pass the #BuildBackBetter plan to build a Civilian Climate Corps. https://t.co/HykpkA93lg

Thanks to the #ChildTaxCredit, we put money directly in the hands of working families, cut child poverty and hunger, and helped families buy the supplies they need to set their kids up for success at school.
Let's pass the #BuildBackBetter plan and keep this success going.
Every child in America deserves a high-quality education. The #BuildBackBetter budget resolution is the first step towards universal pre-K, which will set all of our kids up for success.
These are our friends, family, and neighbors — and New Yorkers are standing with them. It's time to pass the #BuildBackBetter budget resolution and get this done. https://t.co/X3hlL6sRy2
Congrats, Pete and Chasten! I know you two are going to be excellent parents. We can't wait to meet your little one! https://t.co/rWjl0kDgus

Millions of women were forced to leave the workforce during the pandemic. We can't make the same mistake again. The #BuildBackBetter budget resolution is the first step towards guaranteeing universal paid leave for every working family. https://t.co/iBlKKf3F90

Caregivers are undervalued, overworked, and burned out. The #BuildBackBetter plan will be our first step towards giving family and professional caregivers the support and protections they deserve. https://t.co/Zk60mEJWcw

If we treat domestic workers like essential workers, then we have to ensure they get the pay, benefits, and protections that all essential workers deserve. It's time to pass the Domestic Workers Bill of Rights. https://t.co/KvPrzrjXZ3

Millions of Americans across the country are facing record heat waves and devastating wildfires. Some are suffering historic droughts while others are being flooded by intense storms. We can't keep denying reality. We need to pass the #GreenNewDeal to fight the climate crisis.
Sunset cruise on Lake Placid with Jonnie and Theo. ❤️ https://t.co/tduHW5XrEb

The #ChildTaxCredit is already helping families feed their kids. That's why we're fighting to extend the credit in the #BuildBackBetter plan — because no child should go hungry in America. https://t.co/zbOxRqF3I9

Despite risking their lives abroad to defend our freedoms, they faced racism and segregation here at home. We can't make up for the injustices they endured, but we must honor their service and ensure their stories are never forgotten. https://t.co/odwDQdXuRg

The Harlem Hellfighters spent 191 days in the trenches on the front lines — longer than any other similarly sized American unit. They also suffered more casualties than any other American regiment during the war, with about 1,400 killed or wounded. https://t.co/Qyyk8S0HZP

This week, Congress voted to award the Congressional Gold Medal to the Harlem Hellfighters — a black National Guard unit from New York that fought in WWI. Although they served with distinction and honor, their service was ignored or overlooked in their own lifetimes. https://t.co/r6NYRtQKfS

In less than a year we've nearly cut poverty in half. Now let's pass the #BuildBackBetter agenda, create even more good, union jobs, pass child care and paid leave, and help families not just survive — but thrive. https://t.co/lv0CsKo0b3
One year ago today, @JoeBiden chose @KamalaHarris to be his vice president. And every single day, my friend is making America so proud. https://t.co/ux1t3WFL1u
Hello, TikTok! https://t.co/LCqWIkj7lD https://t.co/woc0m2hPyj

A crumbling road can keep you from getting to work just as easily as your child care falling through.

Together, the Bipartisan Infrastructure Bill and the #BuildBackBetter budget resolution will invest in ALL the infrastructure families need to get back to work.

We just passed two historic infrastructure bills investing in everything from roads, bridges, and broadband to paid leave, child care, and fighting the climate crisis. That's how you #BuildBackBetter. https://t.co/Z4odNUdecw

Roads, bridges, and rural broadband.
Paid leave, child care, and universal pre-K.
Clean energy, clean water, and a Civilian Climate Corps.

This week, we're making a historic investment in infrastructure that will benefit every single American.
📷: @NewYorker

This was taken the year I first introduced a bill to guarantee paid leave for every worker in America. 8 years later, Henry isn't small enough to hide behind my desk anymore — and with the #BuildBackBetter budget resolution, we're closer than ever to finally passing paid leave. https://t.co/cpaDznSFyg
We're about to create millions of good, high-paying union jobs. I'm fighting to make sure that every American has a fair shot at getting those jobs. https://t.co/4foEF0S8Hb

The UN #ClimateReport confirms what we're already seeing with our own eyes. From record-breaking wildfires to crushing heat waves, the climate crisis is a catastrophic threat to our future. We need a #GreenNewDeal. https://t.co/8eUIqk8ztK

✅ Paid Family and Medical Leave
✅ Universal Pre-K
✅ Child Care
✅ Long Term Care for Seniors and People with Disabilities
✅ Extending the Child Tax Credit

We're going to make life a whole lot easier for working families. Let's do this. https://t.co/Z3NjOO54yX

At some point in our lives, all of us will need to care for a loved one — or be cared for ourselves. You shouldn't be forced to quit your job when that happens.

We need to pass universal, guaranteed paid leave to protect every worker in America. https://t.co/wNoNPxwYae

We all want life to get back to normal, but that won't happen until we all get vaccinated.

Half of the United States is already fully vaccinated. If you haven't gotten yours yet, now's the time. It's safe, free, and protects you and your loved ones. Get the COVID-19 vaccine now.

If we're going to have a government of the people, by the people, and for the people, then we need to ensure that every vote is counted. We need to pass the #ForThePeopleAct and defend the right to vote. https://t.co/riDCshx7ax

John Lewis risked his life to secure the right to vote. 56 years ago today he witnessed President Johnson sign the Voting Rights Act into law. But nearly 50 years later, he saw the Supreme Court gut it. It's our responsibility now to protect his legacy & defend the right to vote. https://t.co/Y4M7cgXLuY
.@TeamUSA — you're making us proud. 🇺🇸 https://t.co/fScRJ2afJ7

Deeply heartbroken to hear of Richard Trumka's passing. He was a champion for working families across America, and I was proud to fight beside him for the #PROAct to protect our unions. My heart goes out to his family, friends, and our brothers and sisters at @AFLCIO.

Texas Democrats are on the frontlines of the fight to protect our democracy. We need to stand with them now and show that when voting rights are under attack, we will all step up and fight back. Chip in now to be a part of this fight: https://t.co/5jreWHOVTv
Happy birthday, @BarackObama! https://t.co/DA3p2E1JF4

Black women have to work nearly eight extra months in 2021 to earn what white men did during 2020. It's time to close the pay gap for good and ensure that Black women get the pay they have earned and deserve. #BlackWomensEqualPayDay https://t.co/w4RN0ttBds
The COVID-19 vaccine is safe, free, and protects you and your loved ones. Get vaccinated now. https://t.co/VIxPRLsFc9

Leave it better than you found it — that's the rule I've taught my boys when we go out into nature. And if we want to leave behind a livable, beautiful planet for future generations, that's our responsibility now. We need to pass a #GreenNewDeal to fight the climate crisis. https://t.co/w0TaLFLJrc

Millions of women have been forced to leave their jobs to care for a loved one — but that lost paycheck makes it even harder to care for their families.

It's time to pass the American Families Plan and finally guarantee universal paid leave for every family. https://t.co/OIo8ZTg8DN

Millions of Americans have affordable health care, thanks to 56 years of Medicare and Medicaid. Let's open up the promise of affordable health care to EVERY American and finally pass Medicare For All.

On average, women in the United States earn 82 cents for every $1 earned by men. The #USWNT makes as little as 38 cents for every $1 paid to their male counterparts.

Women athletes have earned & deserve equal pay. Today, I introduced the Even Playing Field Act to make it happen. https://t.co/ubsnslfZHY

This is how we #BuildBackBetter. https://t.co/gWlIL7vZYi
“What the military is doing is not working. It’s the same thing every year. We have to get [the Military Justice Improvement and Increasing Prevention Act] passed.” https://t.co/iOHqawTvB9

Students can't succeed if they're hungry — but current SNAP requirements trap low-income students in a vicious cycle that makes it harder for them to study. So today I introduced the EATS Act to help college students get the food they need to succeed. https://t.co/rq3L0vScwb

Yazmin's DACA application was approved. Her father's was blocked by a judge's outrageous ruling. These families deserve to live without fear and uncertainty. We need to pass a pathway to citizenship for Dreamers and undocumented immigrants.  https://t.co/cQW3p9nukq

The Americans with Disabilities Act was a landmark bill, but 31 years later, we are still fighting to fully realize its vision. Today we celebrate what it has achieved and commit ourselves to continuing the fight for equality and accessibility for every American.

When the Americans with Disabilities Act was stalled in Congress, Americans with disabilities came to D.C. and crawled up the steps of the Capitol building to show how inaccessibility impacts them. Their bravery spurred Congress to act, and led to the passage of the ADA. #ADA31 https://t.co/AjFOaEZMof
Overcoming the filibuster. https://t.co/3t87LYheeH

For years, we’ve been losing control over our personal information as companies build major empires from our data.

Over 70% of Americans agree — Big Tech needs to be held accountable. We need a Data Protection Agency. https://t.co/i4xK1LLRJZ

The climate crisis is here — and from raging wildfires to crushing heat waves, we're already feeling the effects. We can fight this crisis, build healthier and more resilient communities, and create good, union jobs by building a Civilian Climate Corps.

Paid leave isn't just something that's "nice to have."

Paid leave:
✅ Improves maternal health
✅ Decreases infant mortality
✅ Boosts the economy

Let's give working families and parents the support they need. It's time to pass universal paid leave. https://t.co/DpVbAk5Dqy

We need to pass the Women's Health Protection Act and stop states from trying to overturn our reproductive rights. https://t.co/YcvQv3n9y3

New York's skies are filled with smoke from wildfires burning thousands of miles away. Climate change is here — and it is impacting all of us. If we want to breathe clean air, we need to act now to end the climate crisis. https://t.co/B29DRu3sK1

"To honor the service and memory of U.S. Army Spc. Vanessa Guillén, and to make justice for all a reality on every base in every branch of the U.S. military, we encourage our elected representatives to voice their support for the I am Vanessa Guillén Act." https://t.co/bQMiCd1aRg
When workers can organize and unions are strong, working families can thrive. It's time to pass the #PROAct.

Paid leave helps workers care for themselves and their families without losing their jobs or paychecks. After nearly a decade of fighting for it, I'm proud that paid family and medical leave will be included in the newly negotiated American Families Plan.

I was lucky enough to meet @ErinForYall and her daughter Lark yesterday, and what she's doing for her family and for voting rights is incredible. I know how hard it is to serve with young kids, but we are so much stronger with her voice in this fight. https://t.co/EOOK3n2PE1

If we had universal paid leave during the pandemic, fewer women would have had to quit their jobs entirely to care for their families. It's time to catch up to the rest of the world and finally guarantee universal paid leave for every family. https://t.co/fkl33J4tMy

Great news—most families will start receiving monthly checks of up to $300 per child today thanks to the #ChildTaxCredit! That's money that will go directly to families that need it to pay for school supplies, groceries, child care, and so much more. How will it help your family? https://t.co/mpYEi7ehgA

A soldier abusing his wife killed a man who tried to intervene. Instead of alerting Army investigators, his commanders quietly reassigned him to a new base.

We need to #PassMJIIPA and remove prosecutions of ALL serious crimes from the chain of command.
https://t.co/6XLlLFe8kh

Corporations and sexual harassers have used forced arbitration agreements to hide their misdeeds and silence survivors. It's time to #EndForcedArbitration, allow survivors of sexual assault and harassment to speak out, and give them their day in court.

Specialist Vanessa Guillén was murdered after being harassed.

Lance Cpl. Maria Lauterbach was murdered after being sexually assaulted.

Airman 1st Class Natasha Aposhian was murdered after breaking up with a fellow airman.

I'm fighting to #PassMJIIPA for them & their families. https://t.co/qzrfknvkAN
That's why my bill, the Military Justice Improvement and Increasing Prevention Act, doesn't just address sexual assault. It ensures justice for victims of all serious crimes — including murder.

It's historic that the Secretary of Defense and the President of the United States support removing sexual assault prosecutions from the chain of command.

But as @JoeBiden said, this is just the beginning of our work. The problems in our military justice system go far deeper.

Texas Democrats are risking arrest to protect the right to vote. We owe it to them — and to every American who has sacrificed to protect our democracy — to step up, pass the #ForThePeopleAct, and put an end to voter suppression. And we can't let the filibuster stand in our way. https://t.co/eaOVSthy1L

Only two Black women have ever been elected to the Senate, and none are currently serving. But next year, we can change that by electing @valdemings and @CheriBeasleyNC! Chip in now to help send them both to the Senate: https://t.co/lhDdu8M57D

Our service members put their lives on the line to defend the fundamental American right of “justice for all.” They should not — and cannot — be denied it. It's time to #PassMJIIPA and ensure equal justice for all. https://t.co/q4HHcKlTXO

Essential workers who worked on the frontlines of this pandemic are more likely not to have paid leave for ANY reason.

No one should ever have to choose between their or their family's health and a paycheck. Not during a pandemic — not ever. It's time for universal paid leave.

At the heart of the For The People Act is the Voter Empowerment Act, a bill John Lewis and I worked on together to protect and expand the right to vote and put an end to voter suppression. It's on us to carry on his fight to defend every American's right to vote. https://t.co/50oX5cp8w1

Your washing machine absolutely does not need access to your phone's contacts. We need an agency to hold big tech companies accountable for how they collect, use, and sell your personal data. It's time for a Data Protection Agency. https://t.co/JYnMs7YzXX
